1
00:00:30,720 --> 00:00:32,960
Li

2
00:00:32,960 --> 00:00:33,720
Li Yang.

3
00:01:04,360 --> 00:01:05,040
Liu.

4
00:01:30,800 --> 00:01:32,259
Which one of you is paying?

5
00:01:32,320 --> 00:01:33,360
I'll pay.

6
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:35,200
Don't worry about it.

7
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:39,120
How much?

8
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:40,920
Over 10,000.

9
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,360
How much?

10
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,120
Over 10,000.

11
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,440
No, no.

12
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,600
No, brother.

13
00:01:47,600 --> 00:01:49,600
He said you have over 10,000 here.

14
00:01:50,000 --> 00:01:50,759
Yes, I was saying...

15
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:52,120
What he's asking you is

16
00:01:52,120 --> 00:01:53,600
how much this meal costs.

17
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:54,240
Sit down, sit down.

18
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,120
Do you understand? He's asking you

19
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:57,200
how much this meal costs.

20
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,050
The meal is free.

21
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:01,440
Free?

22
00:02:01,440 --> 00:02:03,040
What are you doing here then?

23
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,420
Don't be afraid, don't be afraid.

24
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:06,360
Take this.

25
00:02:06,360 --> 00:02:07,320
Okay, that's enough, enough.

26
00:02:07,320 --> 00:02:09,380
That's definitely enough. Let's go.

27
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:11,770
Look how scared you are.

28
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:15,130
Where would I get so much money? I just got out.

29
00:02:16,680 --> 00:02:18,440
Erpang needs to live with me.

30
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:20,180
We need to rent a place.

31
00:02:20,880 --> 00:02:22,440
Then you can bring him back.

32
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,640
Do you need me to write you a receipt?

33
00:02:34,640 --> 00:02:35,360
No need.

34
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,960
I can tell you're decent people.

35
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:38,680
Otherwise I wouldn't dare rent to you.

36
00:02:38,680 --> 00:02:41,000
What if I rented to some thugs

37
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,120
and they trashed my house?

38
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:45,800
Alright then. Carry on.

39
00:02:57,520 --> 00:02:58,440
Brother, I've

40
00:02:58,440 --> 00:02:59,600
never seen anything like this

41
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,460
in my whole life. Such a big house.

42
00:03:03,440 --> 00:03:04,770
Are these all the rooms?

43
00:03:15,440 --> 00:03:17,000
Still living in the same old place?

44
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,120
You bet. They talk about demolition

45
00:03:19,120 --> 00:03:20,520
but never actually do it.

46
00:03:20,640 --> 00:03:21,680
Leaks in winter

47
00:03:21,680 --> 00:03:22,960
and drafty in summer.

48
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:26,000
I'm really afraid one day a strong wind

49
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:27,640
will blow my roof right off.

50
00:03:27,680 --> 00:03:28,960
Then move in here.

51
00:03:29,360 --> 00:03:31,200
No way. This is your home.

52
00:03:31,200 --> 00:03:32,440
Aren't there three rooms?

53
00:03:32,440 --> 00:03:33,760
One for me, one for Erpang,

54
00:03:33,760 --> 00:03:35,200
and one for you. Perfect.

55
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:36,680
It's not appropriate.

56
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,760
I can't disturb your life.

57
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,200
What? Do I have to beg you?

58
00:03:40,760 --> 00:03:41,880
You're already lying here.

59
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:42,880
Brother, that's not what I meant.

60
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,200
What do you mean then?

61
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:46,260
This place already feels like yours.

62
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,329
I know your home is far away.

63
00:03:50,120 --> 00:03:50,880
While you're here,

64
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:52,560
cook a meal for Erpang.

65
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:54,540
Your cooking is so delicious.

66
00:03:55,079 --> 00:03:56,760
I don't have any other requests.

67
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,440
Just one.

68
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:01,640
What request? Don't bring women back here.

69
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:02,770
I can't handle that.

70
00:04:03,800 --> 00:04:05,200
That might be difficult.

71
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:07,680
Well...

72
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:09,760
I can't promise.

73
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:19,240
Let's buy some bedding, toilet paper

74
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:23,000
and daily necessities. Stock up on food and drinks.

75
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:26,000
Let's get some booze and snacks

76
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:28,000
and start our new life.

77
00:04:38,640 --> 00:04:39,760
Which room is mine?

78
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,760
You'll stay here.

79
00:04:42,760 --> 00:04:44,000
No problem.

80
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:46,540
It's so soft. This one's perfect.

81
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,920
Later, I'll take Erpang

82
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:00,440
to Huo Dongfeng's place.

83
00:05:00,440 --> 00:05:03,320
Then I'll go to my night shift.

84
00:05:04,080 --> 00:05:06,440
Why does your night shift end so early?

85
00:05:07,280 --> 00:05:08,540
Isn't earlier better?

86
00:05:09,320 --> 00:05:10,040
I've seen other people's night shifts

87
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:11,240
that last until dawn.

88
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:12,720
That's them,

89
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:13,840
and we're us.

90
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,160
Brother,

91
00:05:15,320 --> 00:05:17,160
are you moving out?

92
00:05:18,280 --> 00:05:19,610
When will you move back?

93
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:21,200
I'm not coming back.

94
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,500
See what happened?

95
00:05:24,680 --> 00:05:25,400
When your brother was here,

96
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,560
you bullied him every day.

97
00:05:26,560 --> 00:05:28,040
Now he's leaving,

98
00:05:28,040 --> 00:05:29,840
and you're feeling bad about it?

99
00:05:30,560 --> 00:05:32,960
After all, my brother is part of our family.

100
00:05:34,200 --> 00:05:35,840
The time your brother spent here,

101
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:36,960
everything you did to him,

102
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,360
he'll remember for life.

103
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,440
Until he's 70 or 80.

104
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,800
Really?

105
00:05:44,159 --> 00:05:45,440
How is that possible?

106
00:05:45,440 --> 00:05:46,560
I'm your sister.

107
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:49,159
No,

108
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:51,080
you're my sister.

109
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,320
Mom's hospital deposit,

110
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,180
why haven't we gotten it back yet?

111
00:05:58,560 --> 00:05:59,520
Oh, I forgot.

112
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:02,040
Give it to me. I'll go get it back.

113
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:03,500
No need. I'll go tomorrow.

114
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:04,480
I'll go change my clothes

115
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:05,680
and see him off later.

116
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:06,800
By the way,

117
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:08,680
that certificate...

118
00:06:10,080 --> 00:06:11,440
We should give it to Erpang

119
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:13,440
to hang above his bed in his new home.

120
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:31,680
Great! That's awesome. Very generous.

121
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:35,840
Bro.

122
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,680
You didn't drink too much yesterday, did you?

123
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:40,409
Do you remember what I told you?

124
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:41,960
It was the day before yesterday.

125
00:06:41,960 --> 00:06:42,720
Right, right.

126
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:43,450
Absolutely.

127
00:06:44,320 --> 00:06:45,800
Cherish it, bro.

128
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:47,400
I'm leaving.

129
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:49,560
You're leaving?

130
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:51,320
Don't go. Stay for dinner.

131
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,720
It's just ready. Come on.

132
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,720
Smells delicious.

133
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,320
I can't.

134
00:06:55,320 --> 00:06:56,380
I have to go to work.

135
00:06:56,680 --> 00:06:58,800
You're working two jobs in one day.

136
00:06:58,800 --> 00:06:59,800
Can you handle it?

137
00:07:00,200 --> 00:07:02,440
It's nothing for a man.

138
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:11,160
You're not working two jobs because of pressure

139
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,680
from Er Pang, are you?

140
00:07:13,320 --> 00:07:14,320
It's just a pair of chopsticks.

141
00:07:14,320 --> 00:07:16,050
Is it really that serious, bro?

142
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:17,480
Just tell me if you need anything.

143
00:07:17,480 --> 00:07:18,320
Alright!

144
00:07:20,320 --> 00:07:21,960
Er Pang, come eat.

145
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:26,920
Are you really leaving?

146
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,040
Bro.

147
00:07:30,400 --> 00:07:31,080
Do you have 6,000?

148
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:31,680
Add another pair of chopsticks.

149
00:07:31,680 --> 00:07:32,610
Sure thing, bro.

150
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:34,400
Do you have 6,128?

151
00:07:35,080 --> 00:07:36,080
Yuan?

152
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:44,320
More or less.

153
00:07:44,320 --> 00:07:44,720
Okay.

154
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:47,159
Wait, keep 200.

155
00:07:50,200 --> 00:07:52,440
Why such an odd amount?

156
00:07:53,560 --> 00:07:55,720
It's because...

157
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,600
Alright.

158
00:08:00,960 --> 00:08:02,320
Just tell me if you need anything.

159
00:08:02,320 --> 00:08:03,450
Come eat, let's eat.

160
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,930
Which room are you sleeping in?

161
00:08:08,960 --> 00:08:10,620
Are you sleeping on the couch?

162
00:08:11,440 --> 00:08:12,770
I see you like this room.

163
00:08:12,800 --> 00:08:13,860
You can sleep here.

164
00:08:14,400 --> 00:08:15,640
Let's sort it out after dinner.

165
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:16,080
Okay.

166
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:16,960
Er Mei said

167
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:19,160
she'll take us to the fish market later.

168
00:08:58,600 --> 00:08:59,440
Sounds good.

169
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,320
Bro, how is it?

170
00:09:06,200 --> 00:09:07,680
The flavor is quite rich.

171
00:09:07,800 --> 00:09:08,560
Of course!

172
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:10,690
That's how a fish market should smell.

173
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:11,560
Brother,

174
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,080
about this fish market,

175
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,480
let me tell you something.

176
00:09:14,480 --> 00:09:15,680
It was rebuilt in '87.

177
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:18,080
It's been six years. I can say

178
00:09:18,080 --> 00:09:19,080
this place is

179
00:09:19,280 --> 00:09:21,600
the fish distribution center for our entire province.

180
00:09:21,600 --> 00:09:22,840
Look at those big trucks.

181
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:23,920
Every day, coming and going,

182
00:09:23,920 --> 00:09:25,320
several hundred of them.

183
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,400
Bro,

184
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,880
let me introduce you to the owner. Come.

185
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:32,640
Er Ge, you're looking good lately, Er Ge!

186
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,240
Just go about your business.

187
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:37,040
Er Ge is here.

188
00:09:37,040 --> 00:09:37,680
Sister Xu.

189
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:39,000
Let me get you some fish.

190
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:39,880
No need, no need.

191
00:09:39,880 --> 00:09:41,280
We just got some big-headed carp.

192
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,160
Let me introduce you.

193
00:09:42,160 --> 00:09:43,040
This is my big brother, Huo Dongfeng.

194
00:09:43,040 --> 00:09:44,760
He wants to do some business here too.

195
00:09:44,760 --> 00:09:46,120
You two should get acquainted.

196
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,250
That would be great!

197
00:09:47,480 --> 00:09:48,610
Go on with your work.

198
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:49,640
Good.

199
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:51,040
Let's go, bro.

200
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:53,130
Everyone knows you.

201
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:54,760
You big troublemaker.

202
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:55,920
And they all welcome you.

203
00:09:55,920 --> 00:09:57,000
What's going on? Have you been bullying them?

204
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:58,120
Who could I possibly bully, brother?

205
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:58,680
Ask around.

206
00:09:58,680 --> 00:10:00,240
Have I ever bullied any of them?

207
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:01,800
Then why are you so respected?

208
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,800
Brother, let me tell you something.

209
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:05,280
Before I came here,

210
00:10:05,480 --> 00:10:06,680
this place was a mess.

211
00:10:06,760 --> 00:10:08,480
Nobody could control the business or taxes.

212
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,400
After I arrived,

213
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:10,920
It got even worse.

214
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:12,240
Once you start working here,

215
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:13,370
you'll understand.

216
00:10:13,520 --> 00:10:15,180
It's different from our time.

217
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:17,560
Completely different from the '70s and '80s.

218
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:20,160
Brother, nowadays money brings respect.

219
00:10:20,920 --> 00:10:23,480
Money gives you courage.

220
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:24,760
I see you've got plenty of courage,

221
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:25,820
pushing me around.

222
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:27,640
Let's go, brother.

223
00:10:28,640 --> 00:10:30,160
This is who I've been telling you about,

224
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:32,120
my big brother, Huo Dongfeng.

225
00:10:32,760 --> 00:10:33,560
I've heard so much about you,

226
00:10:33,560 --> 00:10:35,220
Er Mei always talks about you.

227
00:10:35,280 --> 00:10:35,760
Come.

228
00:10:36,760 --> 00:10:37,640
Have a seat.

229
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,520
Come sit down.

230
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:40,880
Mr. Wu,

231
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:42,040
my brother here

232
00:10:42,040 --> 00:10:42,800
wants to

233
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:44,160
start some business here.

234
00:10:44,160 --> 00:10:45,820
You'll need to look after him.

235
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,000
Look after him?

236
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:47,640
All these years,

237
00:10:47,640 --> 00:10:49,570
you've been taking good care of me.

238
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:52,040
Brother Huo coming to do business here

239
00:10:52,040 --> 00:10:54,520
is actually doing our fish market a favor.

240
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:57,800
In our fish market,

241
00:10:57,800 --> 00:10:59,520
what fish isn't being bought yet?

242
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:01,000
Those silver carp and bighead carp

243
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:02,530
don't have regular buyers.

244
00:11:05,480 --> 00:11:07,800
So can my brother deal in silver carp?

245
00:11:07,880 --> 00:11:09,040
Of course that's fine.

246
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,240
Second Brother has spoken.

247
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:11,760
How could it not be okay?

248
00:11:12,520 --> 00:11:14,520
Er Mei is a righteous brother.

249
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:15,840
Since Er Mei arrived,

250
00:11:15,880 --> 00:11:16,920
our fish market

251
00:11:16,920 --> 00:11:18,160
has become much more peaceful.

252
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,040
These years,

253
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:20,920
the social atmosphere hasn't been good.

254
00:11:20,920 --> 00:11:22,400
If Er Mei wasn't around,

255
00:11:23,160 --> 00:11:25,040
we'd have three fights a day.

256
00:11:25,240 --> 00:11:27,360
All these troublemakers

257
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,800
would cause problems every single day.

258
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,000
Since Er Mei arrived,

259
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:33,730
we don't even have one fight in three days.

260
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,680
He didn't force you to say this, did he?

261
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:36,880
No, not at all.

262
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:37,880
If he dares to bully anyone,

263
00:11:37,880 --> 00:11:38,520
I'll deal with him.

264
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:39,480
Brother, what are you saying?

265
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:40,360
These are all our friends.

266
00:11:40,360 --> 00:11:41,640
Sounds just like you coached them.

267
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,500
What could I possibly teach them?

268
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:44,240
Mr. Wu,

269
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,400
once my brother starts working here,

270
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:47,400
rest assured, your fish market will be even more stable.

271
00:11:47,400 --> 00:11:49,400
If anyone dares to cause trouble in the future,

272
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,040
just let my brother handle it.

273
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:51,680
You just said

274
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:54,080
I'm a righteous brother, and I accept that.

275
00:11:54,160 --> 00:11:54,800
But

276
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,240
these small skills of mine

277
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:58,120
I learned from my big brother.

278
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,640
People out there

279
00:11:59,640 --> 00:12:00,880
may not respect me, Ermei,

280
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,940
but they must respect my big brother.

281
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:05,080
Who is my big brother?

282
00:12:05,280 --> 00:12:07,040
The leader of the Dalin Three Heroes.

283
00:12:07,040 --> 00:12:08,880
A true hero. What makes a hero?

284
00:12:09,560 --> 00:12:11,520
Someone who enjoys helping others

285
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:12,520
and never bullies anyone.

286
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:13,280
Enough.

287
00:12:13,280 --> 00:12:14,280
No, brother.

288
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:16,080
Fine, we've bullied people too.

